{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:13:47.282437+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 9fb9c961ceb3931aef309ec69d5bc51260d7e3bf)", "id": "lc_4866feed-1d4d-4757-88f1-d4a60aa504d6"}, {"type": "text", "text": "const Mock = require('mockjs')\nconst { param2Obj } = require('./utils')\n\nconst user = require('./user')\nconst table = require('./table')\n\nconst mocks = [...user, ...table]\n\n// for front mock\n// please use it cautiously, it will redefine XMLHttpRequest,\n// which will cause many of your third-party libraries to be invalidated(like progress event).\nfunction mockXHR() {\n  // mock patch\n  // https://github.com/nuysoft/Mock/issues/300\n  Mock.XHR.prototype.proxy_send = Mock.XHR.prototype.send\n  Mock.XHR.prototype.send = function () {\n    if (this.custom.xhr) {\n      this.custom.xhr.withCredentials = this.withCredentials || false\n\n      if (this.responseType) {\n        this.custom.xhr.responseType = this.responseType\n      }\n    }\n    this.proxy_send(...arguments)\n  }\n\n  function XHR2ExpressReqWrap(respond) {\n    return function (options) {\n      let result = null\n      if (respond instanceof Function) {\n        const { body, type, url } = options\n        // https://expressjs.com/en/4x/api.html#req\n        result = respond({\n          method: type,\n          body: JSON.parse(body),\n          query: param2Obj(url),\n        })\n      } else {\n        result = respond\n      }\n      return Mock.mock(result)\n    }\n  }\n\n  for (const i of mocks) {\n    Mock.mock(\n      new RegExp(i.url),\n      i.type || 'get',\n      XHR2ExpressReqWrap(i.response)\n    )\n  }\n}\n\nmodule.exports = {\n  mocks,\n  mockXHR,\n}\n", "id": "lc_3b34256c-b193-493a-a227-9b939ddf2192"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "b3b76274-56a1-4a5f-9210-11446b2f46f0", "tool_call_id": "call_dbd5325454a24c72981862cb", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:13:58.524941+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have all the information needed. Here's the full answer:\n\n---\n\n## How the template switches between development and production API base paths\n\nThis is a **Vue 2 / Vue CLI** project that uses **environment-specific `.env` files** to set the API base path:\n\n| Environment | `.env` file | `VUE_APP_BASE_API` value |\n|---|---|---|\n| Development | `.env.development` | `/dev-api` |\n| Staging | `.env.staging` | `/stage-api` |\n| Production | `.env.production` | `/prod-api` |\n\nThese files set a custom `ENV` flag and the `VUE_APP_BASE_API` variable. Vue CLI automatically loads the correct `.env.[mode]` file when you run `npm run serve` (development), `npm run build --mode staging` (staging), or `npm run build` (production).\n\n### How the base path is consumed\n\n**In the dev server (mock backend):**  \n`vue.config.js` injects the mock server via `devServer.before: require('./mock/mock-server.js')`. Inside `mock/mock-server.js`, the `responseFake` function builds every mock route's URL as:\n\n```js\nurl: new RegExp(`${process.env.VUE_APP_BASE_API}${url}`)\n```\n\nSo in development mode every mock endpoint is prefixed with `/dev-api`, in staging with `/stage-api`, etc. The mock Express server intercepts requests that match that prefix.\n\n**In the real app code:**  \nAxios (or another HTTP client) would read `process.env.VUE_APP_BASE_API` to set the `baseURL`, so all API calls are automatically prefixed with the correct path for the current environment.\n\n---\n\n## Mock login usernames and their tokens\n\nDefined in `mock/user.js`:\n\n| Username | Token returned |\n|---|---|\n| `admin` | `admin-token` |\n| `editor` | `editor-token` |\n\n**How login works (mock):**\n\n1. A POST request is sent to `/vue-admin-template/user/login` with `{ username }` in the body.\n2. The mock handler looks up the username in the `tokens` object.\n3. If found, it returns `{ code: 20000, data: { token: \"admin-token\" } }` (or `\"editor-token\"`).\n4. If not found, it returns `{ code: 60204, message: \"Account and password are incorrect.\" }`.\n\n**User info associated with each token** (returned on GET to `/vue-admin-template/user/info`):\n\n| Token | Roles | Display Name | Introduction |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `admin-token` | `['admin']` | Super Admin | \"I am a super administrator\" |\n| `editor-token` | `['editor']` | Normal Editor | \"I am an editor\" |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 622, "prompt_tokens": 14447, "total_tokens": 15069, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 16, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 13952, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0008066922, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002655522, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00054114}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863227-F8EmB9vRucIs69EFBkcQ", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b8-5592-7c70-94bc-ed9d30144bd9-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 14447, "output_tokens": 622, "total_tokens": 15069, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 13952}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 16}}}}]}}}
